cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY

The paper proposes a decentralized algorithm for empirical risk minimization problems using peer-to-peer networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the convergence rate of the algorithm in terms of the algebraic connectivity of the communication network, mini-batch size, and gradient variance, which suggests that it may also belong to the networked systems (cs.NI), social and information networks (cs.SI), or systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.DC, followed by cs.NI, cs.SI, and cs.SY.
